description:
Continuous downpours from 16 to 19 January caused floods and landslides in the Riau province of West Sumatra. A UNDRO/UNFP resident representative reported damage as follows:  

- Solok: 6 people died, 182 families were affected, 500 houses were submerged underwater; 

- Solok municipality: 825 families were affected;  

- Sawahlunto Sijunjung: 300 families were affected; 7 houses were damaged; and

- 6 people were seriously injured, 1,012 families were affected and 1 public building was demolished by landslides in West Sumatra. ([UN DHA, 27 Jan 1989](https://reliefweb.int/node/35315))
